{"author":{"id":"69a73b59e8bca0653e9174a374f9f55c998c9a49750b37bad6bd3960e96b7ca3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1617047017,"nonce":"P8+wF22dC86x4Jo2eSQG/APuAOU=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU4NDM3MzgwOTU=","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/522","origin":"github"},"title":"Get rid of distutils","message":"[Distutils is deprecated and slated for removal from the Python standard library.](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0632/)  Currently, dandi-cli uses distutils in one place: using `LooseVersion` to compare pynwb versions.  The recommended replacement for `distutils.version` is [`packaging.version`](https://packaging.pypa.io/en/latest/version.html); however, its equivalent(?) of `LooseVersion`, [`LegacyVersion`](https://packaging.pypa.io/en/latest/version.html#packaging.version.LegacyVersion), is also deprecated.  Finding the proper version class to use depends on just how pynwb versions are structured.\n\n@yarikoptic What do we know about the format of pynwb versions?","files":null}]}